settings.disclaimer_text: Notice with respect to the Collection of Personal Information: The personal health information on this form is being collected for the purpose of providing care to you and creating an immunization record for you, and because it is necessary for the administration of Ontario’s COVID-19 vaccination program. This information is being collected pursuant to the Health Protection and Promotion Act R.S.O. 1990 c.H.7 and will be used and disclosed for these purposes, as well as other purposes authorized and required by law. This information will be disclosed to the Ministry of Health. For more information, please visit: http://www.health.gov.on.ca/en/pro/programs/publichealth/coronavirus/. This information will be used by Peel Public Health or an Ontario public health unit for the purposes of the administration and evaluation of the Vaccine Preventable Diseases Program. Any questions regarding this collection may be directed to the Medical Officer of Health, Peel Public Health, P.O. Box 667, RPO Streetsville, Mississauga, ON, L5M 2C2, Tel: 905-799-7700.

custom_texts.value: This system is available only for the following eligible groups to book appointments:
custom_texts.extra_value:
First Nations, Inuit, and Métis adults and their household members 18 years of age or older.

    Active health care workers and health-affiliated workers. Check eligibility before booking.

    People identified as having highest and high-risk health conditions. Check eligibility before booking.

    Home care recipients aged 18 to 59.

    If you are not in one of these groups, do not use this system. Instead, find out how to book an appointment for other groups. If you use this system to book and are not in one of the eligible groups listed, you will not be vaccinated and will be turned away.

    If you are part of an eligible group listed above, you can proceed. Have you used Peel Public Health online services previously?

custom_texts.value:
Your appointment at  on  with  is now confirmed.

If you are booking another appointment for a separate person or family member click the 'Log out' button in the top right-hand corner to proceed with booking. 

Here are some reminders to ensure your appointment goes well:

- You will be sent a COVID screening questionnaire before your appointment 

- Arrive on time for your appointment

- Attend your appointment alone if possible; you may be allowed one parent/visitor to accompany you if required

- Wear a short sleeve shirt for easy access to your upper arm

- You will be monitored for 15 minutes after your immunization before you can leave the clinic

- Don't attend on an empty stomach - eat a good meal or snack prior to attending

- Refrain from wearing strong scents (the Region of Peel has a scent-free policy)

- Bring your cell phone and immunization record with you

- Masks are required inside the clinic; please ensure you bring a mask with you


Please complete the pre-visit questionnaire(s) by selecting the start button below.


Best Regards,
Region of Peel
